Main - Class in backgroud
This class contains the main method that is the required start point for any Java program.
Main() - Constructor for class backgroud.Main
 
main(String[]) - Static method in class backgroud.Main
The main method main creates an object of type Library then attempts to load an assignment for it from a from a serialized file that contains that object if one has been previously saved otherwise the program prints to the console that no information is available to load the main then creates an object of the Menu (Jframe) and passes it either the empty object or or the same object that was assigned from the file thus effectively resuming the program from a previous saved run it then sets the menu frame to visible effectively displaying for the user to interact with
